radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated, fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 9 mm; normal visualized lung bases; normal liver with homogeneous enhancement; normal gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands; kidneys enhancing symmetrically; no hydronephrosis; unremarkable duodenum and loops of small bowel; no free fluid or air in the intra-abdominal cavity; no suspicious osteolytic or sclerotic lesions.
